videos.description: Kerwin Roach II rises up for the emphatic one-handed slam.
videos.headline: Roach throws down the hammer for Longhorns

videos.description: Collin Sexton reaches in to his bag for a saucy ball fake and gets the scoop layup.
videos.headline: Sexton uses a sick fake and lays it in

videos.description: Mo Bamba uses his ridiculous wingspan to swat the shot away and then stares down the shooter.
videos.headline: Mo says no!

videos.description: Kerwin Roach is a one-man fast break as he makes a twisting layup for Texas.
videos.headline: Roach makes off-balance layup

videos.description: Alabama's Collin Sexton makes a nice lob pass to a cutting John Petty for the alley-oop.
videos.headline: Sexton finds Petty for the dunk

videos.description: Texas' Jacob Young finds a leaping Kerwin Roach II on the fastbreak for the dunk.
videos.headline: Young lobs it to Roach for monster alley

videos.description: Alabama's Collin Sexton hits the stepback shot over fellow top NBA draft prospect Mo Bamba.
videos.headline: Sexton drills jumper over Bamba

videos.description: Mo Bamba takes the behind-the-back pass and throws it down.
videos.headline: Bamba puts the exclamation mark on fast break

videos.description: Mo Bamba tells Seth Greenberg that he wanted to make sure star guard Collin Sexton did not make any plays against him.
videos.headline: Bamba: 'Not on me!'

videos.description: Texas coach Shaka Smart sat down with Seth Greenberg and Rich Hollenberg and says his team did a great job holding down Collin Sexton.
videos.headline: Smart says he was impressed with his team's defense
